Source: wd
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Sourav Tripathy
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 12), cargo, rustc
Standards-Version: 4.5.0

Package: wd
Architecture: any
Depends: libgtk-4-1, libdbus-1-3, libglib2.0-0, wordnet-base | wd-wordnet-data, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Lightweight word-lookup daemon and CLI tool
 wd is a single binary that looks up word definitions.
 It operates as a CLI tool (wd <word>) or as a background
 daemon that watches PDF text selections and responds to
 global hotkeys. Definitions come from a local WordNet
 database with automatic Wiktionary fallback.
